title: drop fast cookies
directions: Add sugar, chocolate and milk together and bring to a boil. Add peanut butter and stir until melted.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal.
If mixture seems too dry add a little more milk.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper and refrigerate until cookies have hardened.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Blend cream cheese and 1/2 cup butter.
Stir in flour and chill 1 hour.
Heat oven to 325°.
Roll dough into 24 (1-inch) balls and press into 1 1/2-inch muffin tins.
Beat egg, brown sugar, 1 tablespoon butter, vanilla and salt together.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup pecans on dough in tins.
Add egg mixture and sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Bake at 325° about 25 minutes or until set.
Cool in pans.
Makes 24 tarts.

title: cousin mary dee's sugar cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening together, then add the eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour and add gradually.
Can make drop cookies or roll out, but cool the batter first if you are going to roll them out.
Bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.

title: six week raisin bran muffins
directions: Pour 2 cups
hot water over bran and let it stand while mixing muffins.	 Mix
wet
ingredients	together.
Add	wet ingredients to dry ingredients.
Add soaked bran and mix well. Store in
refrigerator.
Will
keep
weeks. Bake at 350° in oiled muffin tins
or
cup	cases,	15
to 20 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook ground beef until all pink is gone; drain any grease. Add chopped onion.
Cook until it is clear.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer.
In a large saucepan, put 4 cups cold water, cornmeal and salt.
Bring to a boil; cook until the mixture is slightly thick.
Add butter; stir it in until melted.
Put meat mixture in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spoon cornmeal mixture over meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Drain beans and sprinkle with lemon juice, salt and pepper. Mix all ingredients together with 1/2 cup salad dressing.

title: cucumber and raisin salad
directions: Add all ingredients in serving bowl and mix well.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding blueberries last.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: beef goulash
directions: In Dutch oven or heavy saucepan, heat shortening and brown meat well.
Stir in Lipton onion soup mix, tomato paste and water. Simmer, covered, 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender, adding more water, if needed.
Serve over noodles.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Cover the bottom of a cookie sheet with the crescent rolls; flatten out and pat to make a solid crust.
Bake according to the directions on the package until they are a light golden brown. Cool.

title: chicken livers and bacon
directions: Cut chicken livers in 1-inch squares.
Cut bacon strips in half.
Wrap livers in bacon, securing with a toothpick.
Place in a shallow pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° or until bacon is crisp. Drain fat.
Serve hot.
Makes 24 bite-size hors d'oeuvres.

title: dandelion jelly
directions: Boil blossoms in 1 quart of water for about 3 minutes only. Drain off.
Add 3 cups juice to Sure-Jell and lemon or orange extract.
Bring to a boil.
Add sugar.
Boil about 3 minutes.
Can seal and process 5 minutes in boiling water bath.
Makes 5 (1/2 pints).

title: cherry delight
directions: Crush graham crackers in a medium size bowl.
Add sugar and margarine;	mix well.
Spread in bottom of large cake pan, evenly. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: spinach salad parmesan
directions: Toss together all ingredients.
Serve with your favorite no or low-fat dressing.
Makes 6 cups.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger and Italian sausage.
Squeeze sausages out of skins.
Add seasonings.
Add tomato sauce, paste and water; stir. Simmer, uncovered, for 3/4 hour.
Make enough pasta to serve 6 to 8.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Make crust with first two ingredients.
Crush crackers fine; add to softened stick of margarine.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate.
With electric mixer beat next 4 ingredients for 20 minutes.
Must be 20 minutes!
Pour over crust.
Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions.
Fold in well drained crushed pineapple and sliced bananas.
Spread evenly over top. Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together using broth from boiled chicken. Cook until light brown on top. Serve with cranberry sauce or giblet gravy.

title: linda kay's peanut butter pie
directions: (I suggest you double this recipe.
I make 2 or more at a time. They don't last long.)

title: baked green peppers and onions
directions: Put all ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover; bake in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together, except corn flakes and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
May be prepared the night before and refrigerated.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Arrange potatoes in pan.
Mix eggs, milk, 1/3 stick butter, white sugar, vanilla and orange juice; pour over potatoes. Combine brown sugar, flour, 1/3 stick butter and pecans.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: spanish squash
directions: Cook onion in a little oil until tender, but not brown.
Add tomatoes, zucchini and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook slowly, adding small amount of water if needed.
Add bay leaf, if desired.

title: poppy's tomato sauce
directions: Put a little olive oil in bottom of pan.
Brown onion and garlic.
Add both cans of tomatoes and sugar.
Top with oregano, black pepper and salt to taste.
Simmer 1 to 2 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Use a 3-quart baking dish.
Stew chicken, cool and debone. Reserve 2 cups of broth.
Combine soups with 1 cup of broth.
Pour over chicken.
Mix melted butter with second cup of broth and mix in stuffing.
Spoon over chicken.
Cook at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Grease pie pan with butter and dust with flour.
Combine ingredients and pour into pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown onion in cooking oil and add ground beef, chili powder, tomato sauce, corn and olives.
Place in mixing bowl and add 1 1/2 cups milk and 1 cup corn meal.
Place in a greased baking dish and top with 1/2 pound grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans or 3 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch) loaf pans.
In large bowl, cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Stir in eggs, pumpkin and water.
Blend in flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and cloves.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into pans and bake about 70 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Heat first 6 ingredients until milk is scalding.
Stir in potatoes.
Cook until smooth, stirring constantly.

title: apple chip cake
directions: Beat together eggs and sugar.
Add vegetable oil.
In large bowl, mix together flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Slowly mix dry ingredients into egg mixture.
Blend well.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Spread into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mash avocados.
Peel tomato and dice to fine pieces.
Chop onion into fine pieces.
Mix these together and add salt and very finely chopped jalapeno peppers to taste.
Sprinkle lemon juice over top of mixture.
This helps it from turning brown.
Chill and serve.

title: fruit cup with lemon creme
directions: In large bowl combine undrained pineapple chunks, undrained mandarin orange sections and undrained fruit cocktail with the flaked coconut and lemon juice.
Sprinkle the instant lemon pudding mix over the fruits and toss lightly to combine.
Chill. Just before serving, peel and slice bananas; fold into fruit mixture.
Serve in dessert dishes; top with approximately 2 1/2 tablespoons Cool Whip.
If desired garnish with tiny bit of grated lemon or grated orange peel.
Serves 9.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar, salt and flour.
Add egg yolks and lemon juice; beat until fluffy.
Stir in milk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites with a wire whisk, gently, until well blended.

title: carob chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, honey and molasses; add egg.
Sift dry ingredients.
Mix together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: dirt
directions: Scrape filling off 1 roll Oreos; crush and save.
Mix pudding, milk and cream cheese in mixer.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Crush 2 rolls Oreos, and stir into mixture along with filling from first roll. Spoon into plant pot.
Sprinkle crumbs from first roll on top. Cover and refrigerate.
Place flower in pot when ready to serve.

title: sweet yams
directions: Mix and bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla together.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well into egg mixture. Blend in apples and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: hawaiian roast bacon
directions: If necessary, remove casing from bacon.
Place bacon, fat side up, in ungreased baking dish.
Stir together pineapple (with syrup), honey, ginger and water.
Pour over bacon.
Roast, uncovered, for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Baste occasionally.

title: roasted peppers siciliano
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Wash peppers and drain well.
Place peppers on cookie sheet and bake about 20 minutes or until the skin of the peppers become blistered and charred.
Turn the peppers every 5 minutes with tongs.
Place hot peppers in a large kettle; cover kettle and let them stand 15 minutes.
Peel off charred skin with sharp knife.
Cut each pepper into quarters.
Remove the ribs and seeds and cut out any dark spots.
In large bowl, combine oil, lemon juice, salt and garlic.
Put the pepper mixture, with or without anchovy fillets, into a 1-quart dish or jar, covered. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Serve as an appetizer, a side dish or use in a tossed salad.
Makes 1 quart.
Excellent with lasagne or other Italian meals.

title: miniature chocolate cookies
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking soda and set aside.
Combine brown sugar and granulated sugar, butter and vanilla extract; beat until creamy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in semi-sweet chocolate mini chips and chopped nuts. Drop by rounded spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Makes approximately 6 dozen cookies.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs; add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well, then add zucchini and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour into loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes. Makes 2 loaves.

title: crab meat canapes
directions: Combine cheese spread, seasonings, butter, mayonnaise and crab meat in bowl; mix well.
Spread on muffin halves.
Freeze just until firm.
Cut into quarters.
Store, wrapped, in freezer. Preheat oven to 350°.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: sunshine salad dessert
directions: Strain all fruit and cut up in small pieces.
In a large bowl, place all strained and cut fruit.
Add sour cream and mix thoroughly.
Add miniature marshmallows and mix.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake in 2 loaf pans lightly greased at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: Select a melon that has a thick rind.
Remove outer green skin and pink flesh; use only the greenish white part of the rind.
Cut rind into 1 inch cubes. combine rind and cold water; soak overnight in refrigerator.
Drain; cover with water and boil 30 minutes. Drain.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt margarine, peanut butter and chocolate chips together. Pour over Crispix mixture.
Put mixture and powdered sugar in paper grocery bag.
Shake until coated.
Allow to cool.
Store in an airtight container.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to
Melt
margarine
in a deep-dish pie pan.
In one bowl, mix 1 cup of sugar, flour and milk.
In another bowl, mix 1/2
cup
sugar and fruit.
Pour batter into pie pan with melted butter.
Add fruit.
Do not mix.
Bake for 1 hour. Serves 6.

title: southern pork loin
directions: For basting sauce, saut onions and celery in the butter until soft. Add tomato puree, vinegar and molasses. Blend well. Place meat on a roasting rack in pan. Brush with part of the sauce. Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours or until pork is tender and juices run clear when pierced with a fork. Do brush the pork from time to time during cooking for best flavor. Cooking time depends on thickness of meat. Makes 4 servings.

title: skippy quick cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In medium bowl, combine ingredients; stir making a dough.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Place 2-inches apart and with a fork, gently flatten each cookie making crisscross pattern on each cookie.
Bake 8 minutes or until lightly brown and slightly puffed.
May be topped immediately with sprinkles, chocolate chips or Hershey Kisses if desired.
Cool on rack completely.

title: apple caramel dip
directions: Unwrap caramels.
Place in bowl with a little milk.
Microwave until partially melted.
Add cream cheese and stir.
Microwave until melted and smooth (add more milk if needed).
Slice apples and dip.

title: spiced zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs lightly in a large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
In another bowl combine flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nuts; set aside. Add zucchini and pineapple to egg and sugar mixture.
Add dry ingredients, stirring only until dry ingredients are moistened. Spoon batter into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: nutty sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine margarine with brown sugar.
Add cornflakes and pecans.
Sprinkle over the cooked mixture.
Place maraschino cherries over top and return to oven for about 10 minutes.

title: banana loaf cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, well beaten.
Add flour with baking powder.
Sift in.
Add milk and soda mixture.
Add 4 mashed bananas and vanilla.
Bake at 350°.
Do not grease pan.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: In a shallow baking dish, combine all ingredients except for shrimp.
Cook, uncovered, in microwave at High for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Stir shrimp into butter sauce.
Cover.
Microwave at High for 5 to 7 1/2 minutes or until shrimp are opaque.
Let stand, covered, for 3 to 5 minutes before serving.

title: apple-nut fruit dip
directions: Beat cheese and apple juice in small mixing bowl until smooth. Cover and chill at serving time.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Serve with fruit dippers.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and apples by hand in large bowl until apples are well coated.
Combine with wet ingredients.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour, or until toothpick comes out clean, at 350° (may be less than 1 hour).
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Good with
whipped cream or ice cream.

title: homemade bread and buns
directions: Mix lard, sugar and salt.
Beat in eggs with spoon into granite dish pan.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add to mixture.
Then add flour to warm water mix.
Only then add flour to stiffen and not sticky; pat into ball.
Leave in dishpan.
Cover with tea towel. Let rise 2 hours.
Pull off about 2-inch.
Roll into ball.
Put in greased pans or into loaf bread.
Let rise 2 hours.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Brush with butter after out of oven and pan.
Let cool and serve warm.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: In a medium sized saucepan, mix the 1 cup sugar, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and cornstarch. Beat in the egg yolks and then the sour cream and raisins. Cook over low heat about 10 minutes, stirring constantly, until well thickened. (Mix will thin on heating and then thicken again.) Remove from heat and cool 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and brown sugar.
Add egg and crushed pineapple (drained).
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to pineapple.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: superfast blueberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to
Melt
butter in a shallow 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Combine
flour,
1/4 cup sugar and milk in mixing bowl;
stir
to
blend.
Pour batter evenly over melted butter. Stir together
berries,
remaining
1/2 cup sugar and water; spoon evenly over batter.
Do not stir.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly.

title: chili con queso
directions: In a large crock-pot, add the ingredients.
Cook on low 2 hours before serving.
Serve with chips.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix
hamburger,
onions,
bell	pepper,
eggs,	cracker crumbs, potatoes,
salt
and
pepper.
Mix	2/3
can of tomato sauce. Bake
for approximately 1 1/2 or 2 hours at 350°.
When done, take out of skillet. Add 1 1/2 cups of water and 1/3 can of tomato sauce.
Thicken with flour for gravy.

title: banana nut bread
directions: In a bowl, cream sugar and butter.
Add the eggs and banana and mix together.
Sift together the flour, salt and soda.
Combine with the creamed mixture; add walnuts and mix again.
Pour into 2 greased and papered loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour in a 375° oven.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Mix 2 packages jello pudding mix with 3 1/2 cups milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread 1/2 jello mixture over graham crackers.
Top with another layer graham crackers and spread other half of jello pudding mixture over that.
Cool in refrigerator at least 2 hours. Do not cover pan with Saran Wrap or waxed paper.
Spread frosting over top and refrigerate.
Should be made at least 24 hours ahead of time.

title: sparkling harvest cider
directions: In punch bowl, combine cider, ReaLemon and sugar.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Chill.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
When mixed well enough to work with, add cheese.
Knead this and put on floured board.
Roll out and cut biscuits.
I melt some margarine in my pan and see that top and bottom of biscuits have margarine on them.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine sugar and oil.
Mix in eggs and zucchini.
Add salt, flour, soda, spices and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 75 minutes.

title: hot dogs roll-ups
directions: Wrap bacon around hot dogs; secure with toothpicks.
Place in crock-pot.
Pour the brown sugar over the hot dogs.
Simmer on high for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onions in margarine.
In a separate pan, cook broccoli according to directions; set aside.
Cook rice.
Combine soup, water chestnuts, Cheez Whiz, rice, celery and onions until the cheese melts.
Add broccoli and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cheese roll
directions: Set cheese out until soft; add garlic powder, red pepper and pecans.
Mix well with hands.
Roll into two rolls.
Sprinkle with chili powder.
Refrigerate; slice when cool.

title: lemon-lime mold
directions: Make jello and mix but substitute 1 pint of sour cream for 1 cup of water.
(Beat some cream with some jello to avoid curdling) and then add 1 can crushed pineapple, drained.
Let set and unmold.
May garnish with avocado slices.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Mix salt and cabbage; let stand 1 hour. Squeeze excess moisture from cabbage. Add carrot and green pepper. Mix together in saucepan the vinegar, water, mustard seed, celery seed and sugar. Boil 1 minute. Cool to lukewarm; pour over cabbage mix and serve. This slaw freezes very well. Make a double amount and freeze half for a future meal and picnic.

title: layered bean dip
directions: Spread on cake platter in order given.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: lemon or orange icebox pie
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth and creamy.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: kraut with dumplings
directions: Empty kraut in a deep pan.
Add water and boil.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to package while browning one pound of hamburger.
Drain hamburger.
Drain lasagna noodles and run cold water over noodles.
Then spread 3 of noodles in a cake pan making a layer.
Spoon Ragu sauce over the noodles.
Sprinkle the hamburger over the sauce.
Then sprinkle the Mozzarella cheese over the hamburger.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Trim off large leaves of broccoli.
Remove tough ends and wash thoroughly.
Cut flowerets and stems into bite size pieces.
Add bacon, onions and raisins.
Combine remaining ingredients in separate bowl; stir well.
Add dressing to broccoli mixture; toss gently.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: quick nut fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients, except nuts, in top of double boiler. Place over simmering water and stir until smooth.
Add nuts and mix.

title: holiday coconut rum balls
directions: In a large bowl, combine crushed cookies, nuts and coconut. Add sweetened condensed milk and rum; mix well.
Chill 4 hours. Dip palms of hands in powdered sugar and shape batter into 1-inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar; cover and store in fridge.
If desired, reroll in powdered sugar before serving.
May be made ahead and stored in fridge for several weeks.

title: meat and veggie bake
directions: Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with strips of bacon. Crumble raw ground beef over bacon.
Slice potatoes and place over ground beef.
Peel and slice carrots and put on top of potatoes.
Slice onion and put on top of carrots.
Pour 1 cup water over all.
Bake at 350° for
1 hour.

title: italian beef
directions: Cook all ingredients except onions on top of stove for 3 to 4 hours in covered pan.
During last 1/2 hour, remove meat; slice thinly with electric knife.
Return sliced meat to broth.
Add sliced onion and cook another 1/2 hour or until onions are soft. Serve as roast or make sandwiches when served on kaiser rolls.

title: orange tea
directions: Pour 4 cups boiling water over the tea leaves and orange rind in a heat-proof bowl and let the mixture steep for 10 minutes. Strain the tea into a pitcher; add the orange juice, the lemon juice and the sugar, stirring until the sugar is dissolved and chill the mixture.
Add the ginger ale; pour the mixture into tall glasses filled with ice cubes and garnish each drink with one of the orange slices.
Makes 8 drinks.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake in lightly greased loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 4 to 5 hours at 250°. (Can be made in a crock-pot 4 to 5 hours.)

title: millie's spaghetti sauce
directions: Make meatballs from the hamburger and set aside. (You can brown the meatballs if you wish, but they cook very well if added to the sauce raw.)
Combine all ingredients except
meatballs and pasta and cook at least 8 hours.
Add the meatballs to the sauce and cook until they are done.
Serve over prepared pasta.

title: custard pie (fruit)
directions: Place in unbaked pie shell.
One cup of fresh fruit may be placed on top (such as rhubarb, strawberries, blueberries, cherries, etc.).
Bake at 350° until set (knife when inserted will come out clean).

title: pioneer skillet bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Prepare a fire so you will have hot coals on the hearth.
Put dry ingredients unsifted in bowl.
Mix in buttermilk and egg.
Add 2 tablespoons of vegetable oil and mix thoroughly.
Put remaining oil in 9-inch cast-iron skillet. (If baking in fireplace, use cast-iron skillet with legs, called spider pan.)
Heat skillet in oven or over coals for 5 to 10 minutes.
In oven, pour batter into skillet and bake 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.
Cut into wedges and serve with butter.

title: hobo potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes, pepper and onion in strips. Layer 1/2 the potatoes, onions and pepper on a sheet of foil. Add 1/2 the butter and garlic powder. Layer the rest of the vegetables, add the rest of the butter and garlic. Wrap in aluminum foil. Bake in 350° oven 1 hour or until tender. Also great, cooked on the grill.

title: roast turkey breast with mushroom gravy
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place turkey in shallow roasting pan. Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over turkey.
Cover and bake until done (165° to 170° on meat thermometer), about 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cut turkey into slices. Serve gravy with turkey and, if desired, with boiled or mashed potatoes.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: old fashioned walnut balls
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Sift flour and salt together; add to creamed mixture.
Mix well to make soft dough.
Stir in walnuts (pecans).
Break off pieces of dough size of walnut; shape into balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet with spatula. Cool slightly and roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 4 dozen balls.

title: baked ahead potatoes
directions: Scrub, pierce and bake potatoes at 425° for 1 hour or until tender.
Cool slightly.
Break in half lengthwise and scoop potatoes into a large bowl.
Beat in butter, salt, pepper and sour cream.
Refill shells.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.
Freeze or refrigerate as desired. Serves 6.

title: german-style red cabbage
directions: Remove outer leaves, quarter, core and shred cabbage.

Core and slice unpeeled apples. Combine cabbage, apples, bacon fat, salt and pepper in heavy saucepan. Add enough boiling water to cover. Cover pan and simmer until cabbage is tender, but still somewhat crisp (20 minutes).
Drain off liquid, reserve and keep hot.

title: crab delight spread
directions: Dissolve Knox gelatine in water.
Warm cream of mushroom soup and mix with the dissolved gelatin.
Add the remaining ingredients and stir.
Pour into 1 quart mold.

title: whole wheat bread pudding
directions: Remove crust.
Cut in cubes.
Soak in water and squeeze out. Place in 2-quart baking dish; mix and add milk.
Put in hot oven. When it starts to bake well, then turn down heat.
Stir often for 2 hours.
Serve hot or cold with whipped cream.

title: hot pizza dip
directions: In a bowl, combine cream cheese, Italian seasoning and garlic powder.
Spread on the bottom of a greased 9-inch pie plate. Combine cheeses; sprinkle half over the cream cheese layer.
Top with the pizza sauce and peppers.
Sprinkle with the remaining cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm with tortilla chips or breadsticks.

title: chicken salad with pecans
directions: Boil chicken until done, let cool and cut into small chunks. Fry bacon until very crisp, crumble into bacon bits.
Chop celery medium fine.
Crumble pecans under each half, is in about 6 pieces.
Open canned mushrooms and drain.
Put in large bowl: chicken, bacon bits, celery, pecans and mushrooms.
Add sour cream, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Mix thoroughly and serve.

title: ambrosia cake
directions: Melt margarine in two 9 x 1 1/2-inch round cake pans in 325° oven.
Stir in brown sugar.
Spread mixture evenly in pans.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, salt and peanut butter in mixer.
Add sugars; add eggs, milk and flour sifted with soda.
Drop small spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Mash with fork.
Bake at 325° until done.
May also be used as icebox cookies.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: congealed peach salad
directions: Blend cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Bring 1 cup of juice to a boil; add to Jell-O, stirring until dissolved.
Add 4 tablespoons hot liquid to cheese mix and blend.
Add to Jell-O mix and blend well.

title: taco dip
directions: First Layer:
Spread 2 cans of bean dip.

title: meatball sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add to meatballs.
Cook in crock-pot on low for 6 to 8 hours.
(Italian meatballs can be gotten from Sam's.)

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and drain. Add all ingredients. Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes. Serve with tostado chips or corn bread.

title: reuben spread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes or until hot.
Serve with cocktail rye and horseradish sauce if desired.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Steam broccoli until done. Drain. Saute onion and pepper in butter. Mix broccoli, rice, onion, pepper and mushroom soup together. Salt and pepper to taste. Pour into casserole dish. Top with grated cheese. Put in oven at 350° long enough to heat through and melt cheese.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Drain and set aside.
Beat eggs. Add milk, salt and mustard.
In a greased baking dish, layer bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour eggs over this.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato-peanut candy
directions: Boil potato in	slightly
salted
water
until	cooked. Mash hot potato, adding as much powdered sugar as it will hold to make dough that can be rolled out.
Add vanilla during this process. Roll out
on
powdered
sugar to 1/4-inch thickness. Spread with peanut
butter
generously.
Roll
up
and	slice. This candy keeps very well.

title: hamburger and macaroni
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Cook macaroni until done in large pot.
Put macaroni and hamburger in square 9 x 9-inch pan or larger if serving large crowd.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over top.
Place in microwave or in oven at 350° until cheese melts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli. Mix other ingredients together. Set aside. Put broccoli in 9 x 11 baking pan. Pour mixture over it. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, uncovered.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix together.
Put in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.

title: gingery pea and noodle salad
directions: Stir mayonnaise, ginger, garlic salt, mustard and soy sauce. Chill. Dice green onions and celery. Combine with peas and water chestnuts.
Cover and chill.

title: macadamia butterfingers
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Lightly grease a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
In a large mixing bowl, beat butter, brown sugar, granulated sugar, egg yolk and nutmeg until light and fluffy.
Add flour; stir to combine.
Pat dough over bottom of prepared pan.

title: grandma's swiss steak
directions: Get the round steak cut a little thicker than the regular round steak.
Cut meat into pieces.
Pour some flour on it and pound flour into meat.
Have oil hot in pan; brown meat.
Add green pepper, celery and tomato juice to meat.
Salt to taste. Let simmer until well done.
Add a little water if meat isn't done and the tomato juice is used up.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Mix together.
Place in paper lined cupcake tins, using about 1 1/2 tablespoons per cup.
Reserve 1/2 cup for topping.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine all and serve over ice.

title: fried ice cream
directions: Roll a scoop of ice cream (any flavor) in crushed corn flakes. Freeze.
Roll out a canned biscuit or pie pastry and wrap ice cream, being careful to seal all edges.
This may be returned to freezer until ready to fry.
Heat oil to 400° and drop ice cream in for 30 seconds to 1 minute.
Drain.
Top with maple syrup and nuts.
Most any kind of ice cream topping will do fine.
Serve at once.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnuts
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: memmie's chocolate pie
directions: Bake pie crust according to directions on package.
Heat milk in double boiler.
While it is heating, mix sugar, salt, cornstarch and cocoa well; set aside.
Beat egg yellows slightly, adding 1/3 cup of the warmed milk.
Pour egg mixture back into milk in double boiler.
Add sugar mixture.
Stir constantly over medium heat until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Allow to cool slightly.
Pour into cool baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: patti's chicken
directions: Beat eggs; add garlic, pepper and diced onions.
Dip chicken breasts in mixture.
Fry chicken until brown, then bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add vegetables to chicken and bake an additional 15 minutes.
Take chicken out of the oven and sprinkle the avocado over it before serving.
Serves 4.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into small meatballs.
Roll meatballs in paprika.
Lightly brown in 1/4 cup margarine.
Drain grease and cover meatballs with cream of mushroom soup mixed with 1/2 can water.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear bread into pieces and put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cook sausage and drain.
Put over bread.
Put cheese over sausage.

title: low-fat jello salad
directions: Cook Jell-O and pineapple juice for 5 minutes after it comes to a full boil.
Cool.
Mix Cool Whip, cottage cheese and pineapple together.
Add Jell-O mixture.
Blend well.
Pour in mold and chill.

title: orange raisin carrots
directions: Combine carrots, water and salt in saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Cover and reduce the heat.
Simmer for 5 to 8 minutes, until carrots are crisp-tender; drain.
Combine orange juice and cornstarch and stir into carrots.
Stir in raisins and sugar. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients until creamy.
Beat in water, egg and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover; chill about 2 hours.
Heat oven to 350°.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten with tines of fork dipped in granulated sugar to form crisscross pattern.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet. Remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.

title: frozen chocolate sundae
directions: Melt chocolate chips and marshmallows in evaporated milk on medium heat.
Layer crushed cookies in a flat 9 x 13-inch dish with softened ice cream on top of that.
Spread the chocolate mixture over the top of ice cream; sprinkle more cookie bits on top of chocolate mixture and freeze.
When set, cut and serve.

title: rich chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix together thoroughly the dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and beat with mixture until well blended.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve with boiled shrimp.

title: potatoes for mr. and mrs. party
directions: Melt 1/2 stick oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together onion and potatoes and put in pan.
Heat mushroom soup and cheese.
Pour over potatoes and onion.
Top with corn flakes and drizzle with melted butter.

title: heath toffee cake
directions: Cook German chocolate cake as directed on package.
When cake is done, while hot, pour milk over cake.
Next, pour caramel topping over cake.
Next, put chopped nuts, then add chopped Heath bar.
Punch holes in cake before adding topping ingredients.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, buttermilk and coconut. Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until browned.

title: million dollar pies
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into prepared pie shells. Refrigerate overnight.

title: coq au vin
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Combine salt, pepper and flour; rub into chicken.
Brown chicken in butter in a Dutch oven or electric skillet.
Add whole onions, garlic and mushrooms.
Cook over low heat until onions brown lightly.
Add wine, thyme and bay leaf. Cook covered over low heat 30 minutes or until tender.

title: gladys' baked dessert
directions: Beat eggs; add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in melted butter. Add pecans and vanilla.
Pour into an 11 x 7-inch pan. Set that pan in another pan of boiling water.
Bake at 325°.
Bake for 45 minutes or until set like a custard.
Do not overbake. Cool.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Can be served plain or topped with whipped cream and a cherry.

title: pizza potatoes
directions: Put potato slices and packet of seasoning mix into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Heat tomatoes, water and oregano to boiling; stir into potatoes.
Mix in cheese and pepperoni (use as much or as little as you like).
Arrange more cheese and pepperoni on top. Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cream squares
directions: Melt butter and pour into cake mix.
Add egg.
Mix and press into 9 x 13-inch pan or baking dish.
Take cream cheese, powdered sugar, vanilla and eggs and pour over cake mix.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: orange cranberry cake
directions: Drain pineapple.
Combine flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Stir in dates and almonds.
Combine pineapple with eggs, cranberry sauce, oil and orange peel; stir into dry mixture.

title: uncooked finger paints
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Add water.
Mixture will be grainy.

title: easy cherry cake
directions: Melt the margarine in an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and milk.
Pour over margarine.
Pour cherry pie filling over dough.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Wash and peel eggplant. Slice into 3/8-inch slices.
Dip into beaten eggs until coated well, then place into seasoned bread crumbs until well coated.
Cook in electric pan at 300° for 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
You may use olive oil, Pam or vegetable oil.
Make 2 rows in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Pour sauce over fried eggplant.
Sprinkle with cheese and sliced mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until slightly golden.
Allow cheese to set for 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 4.
tags: Italian flavored bread crumbs with Parmesan

title: clam chowder
directions: Bring to a boil all ingredients except clams.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Take off burner.
Now, dump in clams and let set while you get another saucepan and melt 4 tablespoons of margarine. Stir in 2 tablespoons of flour and 1/2 cup evaporated milk.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
(It will appear lumpy.)
Take off burner.
Put soup back on burner and pour in the sauce.
Stir frequently and cook for 10 more minutes.

title: valentine party salad
directions: In a medium bowl, combine dry gelatin and cottage cheese. Fold in pineapple, marshmallows, pecans and cherries.
Add Cool Whip lite.
Mix gently to combine.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: indoor s'mores
directions: Butter baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Heat corn syrup, butter and chocolate morsels to boiling in 3-quart saucepan, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal in large mixing bowl; toss quickly until completely coated with chocolate.
Fold in marshmallows, 1 cup at a time.
Press mixture evenly in pan with buttered back of spoon.
Let stand until firm at least 1 hour.
Cut into about 1 1/2-inch squares.
Makes 48 squares.

title: barbecue slaw
directions: Mix with 1/2 large head of cabbage, chopped.

title: quick and easy jello salad
directions: Sprinkle dry gelatin into cottage cheese and mix thoroughly. Add remaining ingredients.
Store salad in refrigerator at least 4 hours before serving.

title: herb dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in advance.
Chill and store and use as desired over salads.
Use 2 tablespoons per serving.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Combine oats and oleo in boiling water and let stand 20 minutes.
Cream together sugars and eggs and add to oat mixture, then add flour, salt, cinnamon, soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bad baked beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
In pot, add beans, onions, bell peppers and remaining ingredients.
Heat on low 15 minutes. Crumble bacon and add most of it to heating mixture.
Put mixture in baking dish and top with remaining bacon.
Cook at 325° for about 30 minutes.

title: thanksgiving potatoes
directions: Place the diced potatoes in a large saucepan and add water to cover.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer over medium heat until tender.
Drain.
Place the potatoes in a mixer bowl.
Cut the butter and cream cheese into small pieces and add to the potatoes. Beat with an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Beat in the sour cream.
Season with nutmeg, salt and pepper to taste.
Serve immediately or reheat in a buttered casserole at 300° for 20 minutes, if you want to prepare them in advance.
Yields 8 servings.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown meat in skillet over medium heat.
Drain fat and set aside.
Blend next four ingredients until smooth.
Stir in meat, cheese, onion and pepper.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt in a large mixing bowl; mix well.
Heat margarine and water in saucepan until boiling.
Pour over dry ingredients; mix well.
Beat in buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and dice eggplant.
Cook for 10 minutes in boiling water. Drain in a colander.
Place in a greased baking dish.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter; stir in 3 tablespoons flour.
Add tomatoes, then chopped onion and pepper.
Add 1 tablespoon sugar, bay leaf and cloves; cook 5 minutes.
Pour over eggplant.
Cover with bread crumbs; add grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: harvest cake
directions: Dice apples.
Mix well with sugar; let stand for 1 hour.
Add flour, soda, salt, vanilla, oil, eggs, walnuts and fruit.
Mix well.
Pour into baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: barbecued pot roast
directions: Rub roast surface with salt and pepper. Brown in butter on all sides. Add water, tomato juice, onion and garlic.
Simmer meat 1 1\2 hours. Mix remaining ingredients and add to meat. Cook for 2 hours more. Add potatoes and carrots the last 2 hours.

title: cranberry conserve
directions: In a large saucepan, combine cranberries, orange peel, oranges, raisins and water.
Cover and simmer over medium heat until cranberries are soft.
Add pecans and sugar; stir well. Simmer, uncovered, 10 to 15 minutes, stirring often.
Cool.
Spoon into covered containers.
Refrigerate.
Serve as a relish with poultry or pork, or spread on biscuits.

title: chow chow
directions: Mix the mustard, flour, oil and turmeric together with 1 pint cold vinegar.
Stir into 6 pints of vinegar and boil.
Add vegetables and cook until tender.
Put in jars and seal well.

title: cheese blitz
directions: Mix well the cream cheese, egg and 1/2 cup sugar. Spread mixture on bread.
Roll up; dip in margarine and sugar.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar with cinnamon.
Melt margarine.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: banana bundt cake
directions: Blend all ingredients together thoroughly in a large bowl. Pour into a "well" greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Turn out on a plate.
A light powdered sugar glaze goes well with this cake.

title: jello pudding pecan pie
directions: Blend pie filling with corn syrup.
Gradually stir in evaporated milk and egg.
Add nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° until top is firm and just begins to crack (about 40 minutes).
Cool at least 3 hours.
Garnish, if desired.

title: pink fluff
directions: Take pineapple, Jell-O and sugar and heat on stove.
Cool. Beat cold milk and softened cream cheese.
Fold into jello mixture.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add meat.
Brown and drain.
Add tomatoes, corn, soup and ketchup.
Top with Tots.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until Tots brown.

title: pineapple icebox pudding
directions: Combine butter and sugar.
Beat until light.
Add beaten egg yolks and pineapple.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Roll wafers to crumbs and add crushed pecans.
Place a layer of crumbs then a layer of fruit, alternating with crumbs on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: In ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan, crumble raw ground beef and season with salt, pepper, onion and garlic powder.
Cover evenly with Tater Tots.
Add the undiluted cream of mushroom soup.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes until bubbly.
Bake at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tex-mex soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, brown onion and hamburger.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat for 10 minutes.
Serve with crushed corn or tortilla chips, cheese, sour cream and shredded lettuce.

title: herbed beef-vegetable stew
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown meat on all sides in hot oil.
Drain off any excess fat.
Stir in gravy, tomatoes, Heinz 57 sauce, garlic, bay leaves, thyme and pepper.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer for 1 hour.
Add carrots and onions; simmer 20 minutes more.
Stir in mushrooms and, if desired, the olives. Simmer 15 minutes more, or until meat and vegetables are tender. Remove bay leaf; discard.
Season to taste.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: beef summer sausage
directions: Crumble ground beef in a large bowl.
Mix the next 6 ingredients together and sprinkle over ground beef.
Mix water and liquid smoke together and pour over ground beef.
Add peppercorns and mix thoroughly, best method is to use your hands.
Divide into 3 equal portions and shape into rolls.
Wrap in foil.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: chicken sauce
directions: Mix together and heat until thick.
Put chicken in oven for 15 minutes at 400°.
Take out and pour sauce over chicken.
Bake in oven for one hour.

title: cranberry dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Serve over a bar of cream cheese.

title: surprise pie
directions: Place eggs, oleo, sugar and flour into blender at high speed for 1 minute. Whether using chocolate chips or coconut, add and blend a few seconds.
Pour into greased pie plate. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted 1-inch from center comes out clean.
Pie forms its own crust.

title: dilly dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in refrigerator overnight before serving.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Blend soup and milk and add all ingredients, except 1/2 cup cheese.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Heat sugar and syrup slowly to boiling until sugar melts completely.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Add Rice Krispies.
Roll into balls with hands and place on waxed paper or spread on buttered cookie sheet and cut into 1-inch squares. Store in fridge.

title: zucchini casserole imperial
directions: Cook zucchini until tender (not mushy); drain.
In large bowl, beat eggs; stir in mayonnaise, onion, green pepper, celery, salt and pepper.
Add zucchini.
Turn into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with buttered breadcrumbs.

title: new corn bread
directions: Blend gently to mix, then bake in greased pan at 425° until brown and crusty.

title: chalupa
directions: Combine in large kettle.
Cover with water; bring to boil. Cover and simmer about 6 hours.
Break up meat and cook, uncovered, until thick, about 45 minutes.

title: banana cream supreme
directions: Place graham crackers in bowl and add butter and sugar. Press crumbs on bottom of baking dish.
Mix sour cream, milk and pudding mix together.
Add whipped topping,
mixing until blended. Spread 1/2 over crumb crust.
Slice bananas over filling.
Spread the remaining filling over that.
Grate pecans over top.
Garnish with raspberries and mint.

title: fireplace potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, onions, parsley and pimiento.
Add seasonings.
Brown in hot fat until golden brown and crisp. Makes 6 servings.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine and pour over Crispix cereal (use a large bowl).
Stir well.
Get a grocery sack.
Shake out the dust.
Take the powdered sugar and pour in the sack.
Dump the cereal mixture in.
Close the top of the sack.
Shake it.
Shake it some more, baby, shake, shake, shake, shake.
Look in the bag.
Is your chow well coated?
If not, add more sugar and shake it, baby, shake it some more.
Pour out onto wax paper or foil.
Eat some.
Eat some more.
Put it in a bowl with a lid and put it in a cabinet.
Say you won't eat anymore.
Swear you won't eat more!
Eat some more . . . get really fat!

title: orange raspberry soup(serve as an appetizer or as a dessert.)
directions: Let orange concentrate and red raspberries thaw overnight in fridge.
Combine all ingredients in blender.
Turn on high for 1 minute.
(Can be made ahead of time and kept in fridge until needed.)

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers and butter.
Pour into well-greased baking dish.
Sprinkle top with buttered cracker crumbs and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt margarine (reserve 1/4 cup). Mix other 1/4 cup margarine, salt, onion, sour cream, soup and cheese in pan until cheese melts.
Put hash browns in pan.
Pour cheese mixture over hash browns.
Cover with crushed corn flakes and pour remaining margarine over all.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: special k bars
directions: Combine sugar and Karo syrup in pot and bring to boil.
Be very careful not to burn, helps to keep stirring.
Take off stove; stir in peanut butter, then add Special K. Mix well and spread evenly in greased pan or dish (14 x 9-inch works real good).
Sprinkle both types of chips on top and top broil in oven just to slightly melt chips.
Remove and let cool.
Cut and serve.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Mix brown sugar, oleo, 2 tablespoons flour and walnuts.
Set aside.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs.
Gradually add sugar, beating after each addition.
Stir in melted oleo.
Add flour mixture, alternately with milk.
Beat until smooth.
Spread 1/2 of batter in greased 9-inch pan.
Spoon pie filling over batter.
Cover with remaining batter.
Sprinkle brown sugar mixture over top and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: seafood chowder
directions: Saute onion and carrots in butter until onion is tender. Sprinkle with flour and stir.
Add water, salt and pepper and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer approximately 30 minutes.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: butterfinger cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Combine flour, soda and salt in a small bowl. Beat sugar and butter in large mixing bowl until creamy. Beat in egg; gradually add flour mixture. Stir in Butterfinger pieces. Drop by slightly rounded tablespoon onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake for 10-12 minutes or until lightly browned. Cook on baking sheet for 2 minutes; remove to wire racks to cool completely.

title: brownies
directions: Cream the margarine; add sugar.
Mix in eggs; add vanilla. Stir in flour.
Add chocolate and nuts.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: In a medium bowl, combine stems, cheese, parsley and dressing. Fill mushroom caps.
Bake 30 minutes or until cheese is melted. Contains 15 calories each.

title: borscht
directions: Chop beets, carrots and onion.
Cover with water in a saucepan and bring to a simmer.
Cook over medium heat for 15 minutes.
Add cabbage, miso and apple cider vinegar.
Cook for 10 more minutes. Add tamari or salt to taste.
Serve hot in bowls with a dollop of sour cream on top.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook ground beef.
Mix the spaghetti sauce and onion together. In a 9 x 18-inch pan, layer the noodles, meat and cheeses until pan is full.
Cook for 20 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: mother's flaky pie crust
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Blend in Crisco.
Mix together vinegar, egg and water and stir into flour mixture.
Roll out and fit into pie pans.
Fill with favorite fillings.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in order. Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.

title: coconut delight
directions: Cut
butter into flour until it looks like coarse meal. Add pecans and press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.
Cool.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add all other ingredients. Place dough in greased bowl.
No need to let rise before baking. Keep covered in icebox and cook as you want them.

title: peaches and cream cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Mix in dry pudding mix.
Pour into 8 1/2 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Place sliced peaches on top of batter.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and peach juice together and pour over top of peaches.
Bake for 1 hour on 350°.
Best when served warm!

title: hominy
directions: Dissolve the lye in the cold water.
Stir in the shelled corn and let stand for 15 hours.
Drain off the lye water and put the corn in a sack.
Rub and wash it in the sack through running water. After the hulls are off the corn, take it out of the sack and cook for 3 or 4 hours or until tender.
Change the water 2 or 3 times while it is cooking.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Place ingredients into saucepan.
Heat on high to a boil. Continue to boil, stirring constantly.

title: raspberry ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in raspberries, pineapple and pecans; blend well.
Spoon 1 1/2 cups gelatin mixture into a lightly oiled 8-cup mold.
Chill until set.
Spread 1 cup sour cream over raspberry layer.
Spread remaining raspberry mixture over sour cream.
Chill until set.
Spread 1 cup sour cream over raspberry layer.
Top with remaining raspberry mixture. Chill until firm.

title: dorito casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet.
Season with salt and pepper.
Drain off fat.
Add mushroom soup, milk, Cheddar cheese soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Mix well.
Place layer of Doritos chips in the bottom of baking dish, followed by layer of mixture, then chips and more mixture.
Place layer of grated cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chili
directions: In separate skillets, brown the meats, drain and spoon into large stew pot.
Then, in no particular order, add everything else. Cover and simmer on medium heat until vegetables are tender.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Drain Veg-All.
Mix with chicken, soup and broth.

title: papaya jam
directions: Measure fruit into 6 or 8-quart pot.
Measure sugar into separate bowl; mix 1/4 cup of the sugar with 1 box of Sure-Jell. Stir sugar with Sure-Jell into fruit.
Bring mixture to full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Quickly add remaining sugar to fruit.
Bring to full rolling boil.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Fill jars.
Quickly cover and seal.
Invert for 5 minutes.

title: ambrosia dip
directions: Drain and rinse cherries.
Drain pineapple.
Place all ingredients in food processor.
Process until well blended or mix well until blended.
Chill 1 to 2 hours. Serve with assortment of fresh fruit or fat free cinnamon star cookies or angel food cake. Yields 8 servings (1/4 cup each).
Has 85 calories, 1 g. fat. Heavenly!

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, cocoa, molasses, cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Add buttermilk.
Add flour and mix well.
Makes a 2 layer round cake or a loaf cake.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes for layer, a little longer for loaf.

title: hamburg vegetable soup
directions: Brown hamburg; drain.
Bring to boil the vegetables. Add the seasoning, cabbage and water.
Bring to a boil again.
Add the rice.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: corn dogs
directions: Boil wieners as you would for hot dogs.
Wipe dry.
Insert stick in wieners if you have them.
If not, serve on plate and eat with forks.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, corn meal, butter, milk and eggs together.
Coat wieners with batter.
Fry in deep fat, heated to 365° until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Good served with mustard.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Chop apples fine. Add sugar; mix and set aside. Mix oil or oleo, vanilla and eggs. Add to apple mixture. Sift together flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and soda. Add pecans. Mix and add to apple mixture. Pour into
Bundt or tube pan sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: tuna and rice casserole
directions: Combine rice, albacore, celery, onion, lemon juice, diced eggs, sliced mushrooms and sliced chestnuts.
Mix curry powder, pepper, mushroom soup and mayonnaise.
Add to rice and tuna mix. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add crumbled potato chips on top.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until it bubbles.
If made ahead, add potato chips last and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: mock clam chowder
directions: Saute onion and chopped celery in butter.
Add cream of potato soup with evaporated milk, water, parsley, chives and white fish. Simmer 1/2 hour.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Crush saltines to coarse meal.
Spread a 1/2-inch layer of saltines in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Layer oysters and dots of butter with layers of crackers.
Add salt and pepper to each layer to your taste.
Fill to within 1-inch of top of casserole dish. Add milk to just cover cracker layer on top.
Finish with a couple dots of butter.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 minutes or until top is golden brown and crusty.

title: easy pot pie
directions: Cut up enough meat to line the bottom of crusts.
Pour a thin layer of mashed potatoes, a layer of peas, another layer of potatoes, a layer of carrots and another layer of potatoes.
Put a pie crust on top and put butter on top of crust.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 pot pies.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese; gradually add pineapple, green pepper, onion and seasoned salt.
Mix well.
Roll into ball and roll ball in chopped pecans.
Chill.
Serve with your favorite crackers. Will keep a week if kept refrigerated.

title: fresh fruit butter
directions: Cream butter, stir in fruit or peel and lemon juice. Refrigerate or freeze.
These will keep up to 3 months in the freezer.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix well.
Make into balls.
Roll in flour and brown in oil. Put in casserole dish.
Add can of mushroom soup and can almost full of water. Cook about 30 minutes at 350° to 400°.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale.
Wait until time to serve to add ginger ale.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak raisins and dates in wine or brandy for at least 15 minutes.
Add milk and bread.
Bring to a boil.
Add beaten eggs, mixed with sugar and vanilla.
Let mixture come to boiling point. Pour into 8 x 12-inch pan, that has been sprayed with nonstick spray.
Put this pan into a larger pan with hot water 1 1/2-inches deep.
Pour melted butter over top and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in 375° oven until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Combine strawberries and 2 c. sugar and bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Add remaining sugar and lemon juice.
Boil 12 - 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir until foam disappears. Let cool, put in jars and seal.

title: squash bread
directions: Beat together the first 3 ingredients.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Grease and flour two loaf pans.
Pour in batter. Bake in a 325° oven for one hour or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes and turn out.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook noodles 10 hours before baking time.
Saute onion, celery and mushrooms.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, dry spaghetti sauce mix, cottage cheese, mushroom soup and eggs.
Simmer.

title: greek chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine chicken, cucumbers, Feta cheese, olives and parsley; set aside.
In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, yogurt and oregano.
Add to chicken mixture.
Toss lightly until coated.
Cover and chill.
Serve on Boston lettuce or whole wheat pita.
Makes 8 servings.

title: angel pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add sugar gradually with vanilla.
Beat until mixture forms soft peaks.
Add cracker crumbs and pecans together.
Fold into egg white mixture.
Bake in 9-inch pan for 30 minutes at 325°.
Cool thoroughly.
Top with 1 1/2 boxes Cool Whip mixed according to directions on box.
Sprinkle with nuts and coconut, if desired.

title: tex-mex meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into a loaf and bake at 350° for about 45 to 50 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, oleo and cocoa; bring to a boil.
Boil 1 1/2 minutes; take off heat and add peanut butter and vanilla, then add oats.
Mix well; drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper.

title: chicken casserole deluxe
directions: Wash chicken and place in pan with 2 quarts of boiling water and salt.
Simmer, covered, until tender.
Drain; reserve broth. Cool.
Remove meat from bones.
Heat oven to 350°.
Arrange beans over bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange half of chicken over beans.
Top with 16 of the saltines, then half of the cheese.
Combine soup, broth, onion flakes and remaining cheese and pour over chicken.
Crumble remaining saltines. Sprinkle over casserole.
Top with mushrooms.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake 30 minutes or until bubbling.

title: sugar pie
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Blend sugar, flour, butter and salt with a pastry blender until smooth.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Add whipping cream and stir "gently" with a finger in a wavy motion.
Do not tear bottom of pie shell.
Mix vanilla and milk together and pour over cream mixture.
DO NOT STIR.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
This will thicken as it cools.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt, flour and cocoa.
Add milk.
Separate eggs. Beat yolks and mix well with other ingredients.
Cook on medium heat until it thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla flavoring and butter.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue from the egg whites.
Bake at 375° until lightly brown.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown meat; drain and set aside.
Blend next 4 ingredients until smooth.
Stir in meat, cheese, onion, pepper and salt.
Turn into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes until brown on top and knife in center comes out clean.
Serves 4.

title: turkey barley soup
directions: Combine stock, onions and barley in Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add potato and carrot and simmer 20 minutes more.
Stir in turkey and peas and simmer 5 minutes more.
Serves 8. Can be served hot over brown rice as a side dish.

title: squash pickles
directions: Bring to a boil.
Add squash mixture.
Boil 2 minutes and can.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Put cooked macaroni in large, buttered casserole dish.
Add butter, milk and most of cheese.
Stir until smooth.
Add salt and pepper.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: grilled lemon chicken
directions: Mix lemon juice and dressing mix.
Set aside to thicken.
With kitchen mallet, pound chicken to 1/2-inch thickness.
Arrange chicken into single layer in pan and cover with lemon mixture. Marinate for 1 hour in refrigerator, turning after 30 minutes. Grill over hot coals 15 to 20 minutes, turning only once.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: In large mixing bowl combine oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat well. Sift flour and gradually fold into creamed mixture.
Add vanilla. Gently fold in apples and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hamburger or sausage quiche
directions: Brown meat; add salt and pepper to taste. Blend together mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch until smooth. Stir in meat, cheese and onion. Pour into pie crust. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Roll out rolls; press sausage on top and roll up and slice. Bake at 375° until brown.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Nutritional Information:
Serving 1 cookie; calories 70; total fat 2 grams; saturated fat 0 grams; cholesterol 10 milligrams; sodium 60 milligrams.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Soften cream cheese slightly; blend in peanut butter, milk and sugar.
Fold in softened Cool Whip; scoop mixture into pie shell. Freeze several hours.
Thaw slightly before serving.

title: homemade pimento cheese
directions: Grate cheese.
Chop up pimentos small and add in with 1/2 of juice with cheese.
Add vinegar, salt, pepper and mayonnaise. Beat with a mixer until smooth.
If not smooth, add mayonnaise.

title: taco pie
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in a skillet until meat is browned, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain.
Add taco seasoning mix and water, stirring well.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Combine refried beans and 1/3 cup taco sauce.
Spoon half of bean mixture in bottom of pastry shell. Top with half of meat mixture, half of cheese and all of corn chips.
Repeat layer with remaining bean mixture, meat mixture and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broiled hamburger spread
directions: Note:
May substitute as desired, including finely chopped cheese.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: In greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch casserole, place the sausage on bottom with the rest of the ingredients on top.
Cover with Handi-Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Bake for about 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Chill and serve with fresh vegetables.

title: mini reubens
directions: On a cookie sheet, place cocktail rye.
Spread with Thousand Island dressing.
Add the sauerkraut, then the meat, placing Swiss cheese on top. Bake in a 350° preheated oven until cheese is melted.

title: sugar free apple pie
directions: Stir all ingredients together; let stand 10 minutes.
Place in 9 inch pie crust; cover and make two slits in top crust.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: lettie's french bread
directions: Mix all
the
ingredients together in large pan.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Let rise for 1 1/2 hours in warm
place, covered;
then punch and work down every 15 minutes, six times.	Divide dough into 3 portions and shape into loaves. Put
in greased pans or cookie sheet.
Cover and let rise again. Bake
at
for 35 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Fry sausage in skillet with pepper and celery until tender. Drain well.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Add all remaining ingredients and pour in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours, covered.

title: the world's easiest tuna casserole
directions: Cook the macaroni and cheese according to directions on the package.
Add soup, milk and tuna and heat through.
You can also add a cup of frozen peas that have been slightly cooked in the microwave.
This is an easy one for kids to do!

title: dill pickle pick-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese, onion and mayonnaise.
Spread on bread (with crust removed) thickly.
Lay bread on damp paper towels.
(Drain pickles.)
Roll pickle up in bread.
Chill overnight.
Slice to serve.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well, let chill 4 hours.
Serve with vegetables, crackers or chips.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Chill cucumber until just before serving.
Combine yogurt, chives, onions, salt and pepper and chill well to blend flavors. Place cucumber on a serving dish and top with dollops of the chilled dressing.
Sprinkle with dill.
For variety, add to the dressing mushrooms (sliced).

title: rice meat balls
directions: Combine Minute rice with beef, egg, onion, salt, margarine, pepper and 1/2 cup tomato juice.
Mix lightly.
Shape mixture into 18 balls and place in skillet.
Add sugar to remaining 2 cups tomato juice.
Pour juice over meat balls in skillet.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 15 minutes, basting occasionally.

title: old west bean pot
directions: Combine baked beans, kidney beans, navy beans, green pepper, tomatoes and seasoning mix in 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes until hot and bubbling.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: w.w. tuna and bean special
directions: Drain beans.
Put in small baking dish.
Mix tuna with beans. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Put in oven for a few minutes to melt cheese and warm beans and tuna through (350° for about 10 to 15 minutes).

title: glazed carrots(france)
directions: Cut carrots into 2-inch pieces.
Heat carrots and remaining ingredients except parsley to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until tender, about 25 minutes.
Remove carrots and boil rapidly to reduce liquid to glaze consistency.
Add carrots; turn to coat evenly with glaze.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: yummy bars
directions: Combine candy bar, peanut butter and marshmallows in saucepan. Heat until melted, stirring to mix well.
Fold in cereal.
Press into greased 9 x 9-inch dish.
Let stand until cool.
Cut into bars.
Yields 30 servings.

title: frosted pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix all ingredients and drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Saute diced onion, celery and carrot in the butter until tender.
Add chicken stock, ginger, pepper and cauliflower.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until cauliflower is tender.
Puree soup in blender.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix all together; pour into 2 (8-inch) or 1 (9 x 13-inch) greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, margarine and the 3 tablespoons sugar. Press in 13 x 10-inch pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes. Set aside.
Mix Jell-O, boiling water and berries; stir until dissolved.
Cool in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Mix softened cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over pretzel mixture and pour cooled Jell-O over.
Refrigerate; let set 4 to 6 hours.
You may top it with more Cool Whip if desired.
Serves 8 people.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Drain crab meat and remove shells; set aside.
In a large bowl, mix together all ingredients, fold in crab meat.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly and golden.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: savory spaghetti  sauce
directions: In Dutch oven, cook ground beef and onion until meat is browned and onion is tender; drain.
Add next eight ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.
Yields 4 to 6 servings, about 1 quart.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients well.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill well.

title: lemon icebox pudding
directions: Beat together and freeze in refrigerator tray for 1 hour or more the 3 egg yolks, sugar and juice of 1 1/2 lemons.

title: gobs
directions: Cream the sugar, Crisco and eggs together.
Add buttermilk, water and vanilla.
Sift together the remaining ingredients and add.
Drop from spoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes.

title: jello pudding cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as on box and bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Remove and poke holes quickly down through cake with round handle of wooden spoon.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Mix in a small bowl.
In another bowl, beat slightly 1 egg white.
Add, a few at a time, 1 cup pecans.
Rub the pecans in the egg white with your fingers to coat them thoroughly.
Drop into the bowl of sugar and spices and coat each nut completely.
Place on a buttered cookie sheet.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°.
Check last few minutes to avoid scorching.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Mix berries and sugar; mix Sure-Jell and water. Bring water and Sure-Jell to boil and cook for 1 minute. Pour cooked mixture over sweetened berries, stirring for 3 minutes. Pour into freezer containers and let stand 24 hours, then place in freezer.

title: ladies delight
directions: Combine tuna and mayonnaise in bowl and mix well.
Place bread on cookie sheet and toast in broiler on one side.
Remove from broiler and turn toasted side down.
Spread bread with tuna mixture; place tomato slices on "open face" sandwiches.
Top with slices of Cheddar cheese.
Return to broiler and watch closely until cheese starts to melt and seems a bit bubbly.
Serve.

title: hollywood chicken
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet.
Add chicken noodle soup and remaining ingredients, except potato chips.
Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Crush the potato chips and spread them in a 9 x 11-inch baking pan.
Reserve a few chips for garnish.
Pour hot mixture over chips; sprinkle remaining chips over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: broiled salmon steaks
directions: Buy two salmon steaks from the fresh seafood section of the supermarket.
Rinse with cold water and pat dry.
Preheat broiler (if using Jenn-Air, spray grill with Pam).
Lightly sprinkle both sides with garlic salt and fresh lime 15 minutes before cooking. Use more lime during cooking to prevent drying.
Turn twice at least.
Broil for a total of 10 to 12 minutes.

title: louisburg chicken pie
directions: In large saucepan or Dutch oven, combine chicken or turkey with onions, celery, peppercorns and water.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes or until poultry is tender.
Remove from stock.
Strain stock and set aside to cool (about 3 cups).
Discard onion, celery and peppercorns.
Skin and debone poultry, cut into bite-sized pieces; set aside.

title: 3-point nacho spread
directions: Blend beans and 1/4 cup salsa in blender or food processor. Spoon into a 1-quart serving bowl.
In small bowl, stir together 1/4 cup salsa and sour cream.
Drop by spoonfuls over beans. Spread to cover.
Spoon remaining salsa over sour cream.
Sprinkle with cheese and cilantro.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 24 hours.
Serve with reduced-fat crackers or baked Tostitos.

title: agua de melon
directions: In the blender put melon, sugar and water; blend until it is pureed.
Ready to serve.

title: coconut pound cake(the nashville cookbook)
directions: Butter a 10-inch tube pan.
Line bottom with waxed paper.
In mixing bowl, beat butter, shortening and 3 cups of the sugar until creamy, about 4 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 2 minutes after each.
Sift flour with salt; stir in flour in thirds alternating with milk.
Add almond extract and 1/2 teaspoon coconut flavor, then fold in coconut.
Place in cold oven; set oven to 350° and bake until cake tester comes out clean, about an hour and 15 minutes.
Place cake on wire rack.
In small pan, bring remaining 1 cup sugar, 1 cup water and 1 teaspoon flavor to a boil, about 1 minute.
Pour syrup over hot cake.
Cool 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove cake from pan to a rack or plate after sugar syrup has soaked into cake.
Eat and enjoy.
Makes 1 (10-inch) cake.

title: ribbon cake
directions: Put 1/2 applesauce in 2 separate bowls.
Mix red Jell-O in one and green in the other.
Layer crackers in a dish (will be 4 crackers).
Then spread the red Jell-O on top, crackers, then green Jell-O until all is used up.
Put Cool Whip on top, if desired.
Cool.
Cut into thin slices.
Good for the holidays!

title: tropical fruit pie
directions: Bake
pie shell.
Line bottom with toasted pecans.
Slice bananas on top of this.
Boil together pineapple, sugar and cornstarch until thickens.
Cool.
Pour on top of bananas.
Top with Dream Whip.

title: honolulu chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine preserves, barbecue sauce, onions and soy sauce.
Pour over the chicken breasts.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Add water chestnuts and green pepper for final 10 minutes.

title: blueberry boy bait
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients together until it resembles coarse meal.
Remove a cup for topping and set aside.
Add baking powder, eggs, milk, salt and vanilla; mix until smooth.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add blueberries.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: *low-cholesterol pound cake*
directions: Cream the margarine, shortening and sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add egg white; beat well.
Add egg substitute; beat well.
Add flour alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Add flavorings.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: Combine broth and veggies in big pot.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Blend milk and flour together and stir into veggie mixture, cooking until slightly thickened. Add seasonings and cheese.
Simmer until cheese melts.
Serves 4.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix together in order.

title: chicken a la king casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.

title: creole seafood gumbo
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan; blend in flour and cook over low heat, stirring constantly until dark brown.
Add liquid, okra, tomatoes, onion, pepper, Tabasco sauce (optional), thyme and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil.
Then cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add seafood and cook 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve in soup bowls with mound of hot rice in center.
Serves 6.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Mix
in order given except the Cool Whip and pour in an ungreased
pan.
This
can	be
baked in same pan or casserole dish
that	it's mixed in.	Bake at 325° until juice thickens. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: easy deep dish pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan or cookie sheet.
Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms; beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Gently smooth dough into ball on floured cloth-covered board.
Knead 20 times.
Pat dough in bottom and up sides of pan with floured hands.
Or roll into 13 x 10-inch rectangle and place on cookie sheet; pinch edges of rectangle, forming 3/4-inch rim.

title: chocolate pies(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well, then add egg yolks, margarine, 1 teaspoon vanilla and Pet milk.
Put milk in quart jar and finish filling jar up with water plus about half more can of water.
Mix all together and cook on medium heat, stirring all the time, until it becomes thick and begins to boil.
Pour in two cooked pie shells.
Beat egg whites.
Add a little vanilla and about 3 or 4 tablespoons sugar.
Put on top of chocolate pies and put in oven; cook at about 300° until golden brown.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Crush crackers.
Add melted oleo and sugar; press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Save some for garnish.
Blend orange juice and milk; stir in Cool Whip and oranges.
Fold in; do not beat.
Pour over crumb crust.
Top with reserved crumbs.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: apricot balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Make into 1-inch balls.
Can be frozen.

title: rejoice cake
directions: Mix flour, soda, cinnamon and salt. Beat oil, sugar and eggs thoroughly. Add flour mixture. Beat until smooth. Add pineapple, carrots, 1/3 cup coconut and nuts. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan. Cool on rack.

title: stuffed cabbage leaves
directions: Combine meats and saut with onion in butter until lightly browned. Add rice, dill, thyme, salt and pepper and mix well. Place cabbage leaves in boiling water for 1 minute. Drain and pat dry. Spoon meat mixture on center of leaves; fold over envelope fashion and secure with toothpicks. Place in greased shallow baking dish; pour tomato sauce over, cover and bake in a slow oven (325°) for 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: oriental beef casserole
